⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Nigredo
node ALC · ALC · ⟦Nigredo:ALC:b90693⟧

WHO   — Nigredo — the blackening · death
WHAT  — The death that begins the Work — calcination and rotting down to first matter, the prima materia, before anything can be reborn.
WHERE — ALC · The Great Work  Framework inputs: Alchemy, catalogued by ROOT0  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because nothing is perfected without first being broken down; the Work begins in dissolution and despair.
HOW   — By burning, rotting, and dissolving the starting material to a uniform black — chemically a real charring, symbolically the dark night of the soul.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Everything begins in the black — the rot is not the failure of the Work, it is the first step of it.

